==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pat
<hw>Pat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Patted</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Patting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. G. <ets>patschen</ets>,
Prov. G. <ets>patzen</ets>, to strike, tap.]</ety> <def>To strike gently
with the fingers or hand; to stroke lightly; to tap; <as>as, to
<ex>pat</ex> a dog</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gay <qex>pats</qex> my shoulder, and you vanish quite.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pat
<hw>Pat</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A light, quik blow or
stroke with the fingers or hand; a tap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small mass, as of butter, shaped by
pats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It looked like a tessellated work of <qex>pats</qex> of
butter.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pat
<hw>Pat</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <ets>pat</ets> a light blow, D.
<ets>te pas</ets> convenient, pat, where <ets>pas</ets> is fr. F.
<ets>passer</ets> to pass.]</ety> <def>Exactly suitable; fit;
convenient; timely.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pat</xex> allusion.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Pat
<hw>Pat</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a pat manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I foresaw then 't would come in <qex>pat</qex> hereafter.</q>
<rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

